Bharti Falls in Mumbai Trading After Profit Declines, Missing Estimates

-- B y   H a r i   G o v i n d
-- 
2011-05-05T03:46:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/bharti-falls-in-mumbai-trading-after-profit-declines-missing-estimates.html
Bharti Airtel Ltd. (BHARTI) ,  India ’s biggest
mobile-phone operator, fell as much as 4.5 percent in Mumbai
after reporting fourth-quarter profit that missed analysts’
estimates.  Net income in the three months ended March 31 dropped to 14
billion rupees from 20.4 billion rupees a year earlier, it said
in a statement to the Bombay Stock Exchange today. Analysts
surveyed by Bloomberg had estimated a profit of 16.3 billion
rupees.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hari Govind at 
 hgovind@bloomberg.net  